      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "No worries at all! Pitot tubes can fail or give incorrect readings due to a variety of reasons. Blockages are indeed one of the most common issues. If debris, ice, or even insects get stuck in the tube, it can prevent the air from flowing freely, leading to inaccurate readings. Other potential problems include damage to the tube itself, which can cause leaks or distortions in the pressure readings. Additionally, the pitot tube can become misaligned, leading to incorrect measurements. Regular maintenance and inspections are crucial to ensure the pitot tube is functioning correctly and providing accurate airspeed readings. So, always keep an eye out for any signs of trouble, and don't hesitate to consult the maintenance manual for guidance on troubleshooting and repairs. And remember, just like a goblin needs to keep his tools in good shape to fly properly, so does a pilot need a well-maintained pitot tube to fly safely!",
